[
    {
        "text": "One man’s neuron is another man’s knowledge.",
        "start": 0.35,
        "duration": 2.659
    },
    {
        "text": "That’s the stance of the Allen Institute  for Brain Science",
        "start": 3.009,
        "duration": 4.631
    },
    {
        "text": "which released the first open access database",
        "start": 7.64,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "of live human brain cells,",
        "start": 10.84,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "including data on the electrical properties",
        "start": 14.1,
        "duration": 3.02
    },
    {
        "text": "of nearly 300 cortical neurons",
        "start": 17.12,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "taken from 36 patients.",
        "start": 19.3,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "Plus 3D reconstructions of 100 of those cells.",
        "start": 22.92,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "Working with neurosurgeons,",
        "start": 27.58,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "the Institute acquired healthy cells from the cortex",
        "start": 28.72,
        "duration": 3.229
    },
    {
        "text": "—the outermost layer of the brain—",
        "start": 31.949,
        "duration": 2.391
    },
    {
        "text": "from patients undergoing surgery",
        "start": 34.34,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "for epilepsy or brain tumors.",
        "start": 36.68,
        "duration": 1.69
    },
    {
        "text": "Normally considered medical waste,",
        "start": 38.37,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "these rescued tissues will provide scientists",
        "start": 40.329,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "with a unique resource",
        "start": 42.809,
        "duration": 1.171
    },
    {
        "text": "for understanding the human brain.",
        "start": 43.98,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "That’s because many studies currently rely on dead",
        "start": 46.149,
        "duration": 4.031
    },
    {
        "text": "--not living-- human tissue",
        "start": 50.19,
        "duration": 1.989
    },
    {
        "text": "or on brain cells from animals like mice.",
        "start": 52.18,
        "duration": 2.66
    }
]